  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>This mega-resort offers the Maximum Vegas experience, with its award-winning restaurants, 170,000 square feet of gaming area, five outdoor pools, including a gently flowing river, private cabanas, cocktail service and a seasonal restaurant. The 30,000 square feet Grand Spa and Salon features a fitness center and full service spa. The resort is also home to the 16,800-seat Grand Garden Arena where it hosts world-class concerts and headliners. There are numerous bars and lounges including Studio 54 and the ultralounge, Tabu. The entertainment continues with La Femme and Cirque du Soleil's, KÃ€ productions. The Lion Habitat showcases lions roaming in a jungle environment, guests can view the lions through a long see-through walkway. Two elegantly appointed wedding chapels are on property. Diverse shopping can be found along the Studio Walk or in the lower level of the main lobby in the Star Lane Shops. The  Monorail station at MGM Grand provides easy access to other Las Vegas Strip hotels.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is centrally located on the Las Vegas Strip, only three miles from McCarran International Airport and four miles from Las Vegas Convention Center.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>The elegant suites are very large, 950 sq ft, separate living room, two bathrooms and decorated in classic motifs. Each room is accessorized with a custom black-and-white marble bathroom, jacuzzi tub,luxurious cotton towels and spacious closets. All rooms are equipped with ironing board, hairdryer, in-room safe, two remote control flat screen television, and alarm clock.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>This mega-hotel is clad in emerald-green glass consisting of four 30-story towers, and is guarded by a 100,000 pound 45-foot-tall bronze lion at the front entrance. It is set on 115 acres of lush land that features a 6.6-acre coconut-grove garden with five pools, world-class spas, and a quarter-mile river.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The hotel offers endless dining options from casual to elegant, from all-you-can-eat buffets to specialty restaurants.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The vast marble lobby is adjacent to the immense casino.</Text>
  </Description>
